title: Air Jordan 1 High Zoom Comfort 'Multi-Color'
description: Introducing the new Air Jordan 1 High Zoom Comfort Anthracite – the perfect blend of style and comfort for any occasion. This shoe is designed to give wearers a truly unique look each time they put it on, thanks to its bold multicolored design. Crafted with leather, Durabuck, suede, and denim materials in shades of white, red, gold, aqua and black, this sneaker is brimming with attitude. Comfort is also at play here; an inset Swoosh, tongue with exposed foam edges and Zoom Air sole promise endlessly soft cushioning with every step you take. Whether you’re exploring the city or grabbing coffee with your friends, the Air Jordan 1 High Zoom Comfort Anthracite offers a winning combination of fashion and practicality that will get you noticed wherever you go.

title: Air Jordan 1 High Zoom Comfort 'Pumpkin Spice'
description: Introducing the Air Jordan 1 High Zoom Comfort ‘Pumpkin Spice’. This updated sneaker icon showcases autumnal hues on smooth black suede and textured suede overlays in a subtle orange finish. A cut-out Swoosh reveals a crisp white underlay, while a retro Wings logo is stamped in black on the lateral collar flap. Plush exposed foam on the collar and tongue provides a comfortable fit, while a Zoom Air unit delivers responsive cushioning underfoot. Perfect for fall, this sneaker is sure to be a hit this season!

title: Air Jordan 1 High Zoom Comfort 'Chicago Bulls'
description: Introducing the Air Jordan 1 High Zoom Comfort Patent Chicago, a sleek and stylish sneaker for women who put a premium on performance and comfort. With an iconic color scheme inspired by none other than the Chicago Bulls, this shoe has an extremely eye-catching design that will elevate any outfit. The all-leather upper, in white and black with red patent leather overlays at the forefoot and collar gives it a unique visual appeal, while the black toe box, heel counter, Swoosh, ankle collar and Win(GS) logo keep things unified. Zoom Air branding is featured on the tongue tag with a convenient pull tab finish off this hard-to-ignore look. Underfoot, the midsole is finished in sail to complete the aesthetic taste. But that’s not even the best part; Experience airy cushioning provided by a Zoom Air unit for maximum comfort throughout your day! Don’t miss out on this modern classic – Get yours today!

title: Air Jordan 9 Retro 'Racer Blue'
description: Air Jordan 9 Retro “Racer Blue” is composed by a black upper and speckled black and white rope laces.  The heel globe logo and the Jumpman on the midsole are both in royal blue color. Finally finalize the look with a black midsole and white rubber outsole.

title: Air Jordan 9 Retro 'Particle Grey'
description: The Air Jordan 9 Particle Grey is a retro sneaker with a modern twist. This updated version of the '90s classic features a breathable black textile upper, speed laces, and tonal stitch detailing. The nubuck mudguard in a neutral grey finish wraps around the heel and extends up the mid-cut collar. Contrasting hits of crimson land on the sneaker's branding elements, including an Air Jordan tongue tag and a molded Jumpman emblem at the heel. Whether you're hitting the court or just hitting the streets, this sneaker is sure to turn heads.

title: Air Jordan 9 Retro  'Black Dark Charcoal University Gold'
description: The Air Jordan 9 Retro 'Dark Charcoal University Gold' is a great choice for those who want a low-key shoe that still makes a statement. The dark grey nubuck upper is contrasted by hits of University Gold, making this shoe perfect for fans of the Bulls or MJ himself. The Jumpman icon on the lateral midsole and embroidered '23' on the back heel are both standout features, while the webbing pull tab makes this shoe easy to slip on and off. Whether you're hitting the court or just running errands, the Air Jordan 9 Retro 'Dark Charcoal University Gold' is a comfortable and stylish choice.

This vibrant red sneaker features a textile upper, speed lacing system, and tonal patent leather on the mudguard, collar, and heel. Black accents include the tongue tag, molded eyelets, and pull loop at the heel. A glossy red polyurethane midsole and black rubber outsole complete the look of this stylish sneaker.

title: Air Jordan 3 Retro 'Desert Elephant'
description: The Air Jordan 3 Retro 'Desert Elephant' is an iconic colorway of one of the most beloved basketball shoes ever created. Originally released in 1988, these shoes highlight the legendary style and craftsmanship that distinguished the Jordan brand from its competitors. Now they're back, offering up a fresh take on the gleaming Desert Elephant print Durabuck upper with Black and Cement Grey accents. This enduring classic proudly offers fans a mix of premium performance and style to keep them at peak performance on or off the court. With timeless Nike styling and the signature Jumpman embroidery on the collar, this iconic silhouette looks as good as it feels. Get your hands on this timeless classic—the Air Jordan 3 Retro 'Desert Elephant'—and experience why it has sneakerheads everywhere rejoicing, year after year.

title: Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'Royal' 2017
description: Did you know that the first time anyone ever saw Michael Jordan wearing Air Jordan 1 sneakers was in a 1985 Nike poster? That's right - the iconic photo of MJ wearing the Air Jordan 1 Royals was the very first time that the world saw him in Air Jordans. And as it turns out, the Royals are actually Jordan's favorite colorway of the Air Jordan 1. He chose them to be the first colorway available for purchase, and they're also the only one of the Top 3 Air Jordan 1 Retro colorways that he never wore on the court. The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG Royals have been released three times since 1985 - in 2001, 2013, and 2017.

Sockliners feature a parquet floor print in tribute to the old Boston Garden, making this sneaker perfect for any young MJ fan.

title: Off-White x Air Jordan 5 Retro SP 'Sail'
description: The Air Jordan 5 Retro SP PS 'Sail' is a special edition shoe made for little kids by world-renowned designer Virgil Abloh. This unique take on the classic Retro 5 model features semi-translucent textile in an ivory hue, with a reflective silver finish on the tongue. The left tongue boasts a large circular cut-out, and these same details can be seen on the midfoot and collar. Other signature Virgil touches include a plastic zip tie and lines of Helvetica text on the medial quarter panel. To top it all off, this sneaker sits atop a pre-yellowed translucent rubber outsole for grippy traction no matter where you go.

title: Air Jordan 11 Adapt 'White'
description: The Air Jordan 11 Adapt 'White' celebrates the 25th anniversary of the iconic basketball shoe with a modern update. The original design DNA remains intact, with a semi-translucent textile upper and white patent leather overlay. The midsole houses luminescent Adapt buttons that control the Nike Adapt lace engine. Users can make adjustments through the Nike Adapt app, including changing the colors and flashing patterns of the lights on the buttons. The result is a shoe that looks great on or off the court, making it a must-have for any fan of MJ's signature line.

title: Air Jordan 12 Retro 'Taxi' 2013
description: The Air Jordan 12 Retro 'Taxi' 2013 is a true classic sneaker. First released in 1996, the Air Jordan 12 Retro 'Taxi' 2013 is based on the OG white/black colorway worn by Michael Jordan himself during the 1996-97 NBA regular season. The sneaker features beautiful metallic gold eyelets and a black outsole with a carbon fiber shank that references the black and yellow of NYC Taxi cabs. The 'Taxi' was first retroed in 2008 as part of Nike's Countdown Collection, and was also given the low-top treatment in 2011. If you're a true sneakerhead, the Air Jordan 12 Retro 'Taxi' 2013 is a must-have in your collection!

title: Air Jordan 3 Retro 'Hall of Fame'
description:
When it comes to iconic sneakers, it doesn't get much more legendary than the Air Jordan 3 Retro. First released in 2006 in support of Hurricane Katrina relief efforts, this shoe is making a comeback today to honor both Michael Jordan's legacy in this humanitarian effort and his 2009 inclusion in the Naismith Memorial Basketball Hall of Fame.

Featuring a white leather upper with cement grey and elephant print details, black and Fire Red accents, and the iconic Jumpman logo on the heel, this sneaker is a true classic. Whether you're a basketball fan or just a fan of great sneakers, the Air Jordan 3 Retro is a must-have for any collection. Order yours today and help support a great cause!

title: Air Jordan 3 Retro 'Fire Red' 2013
description: If you're a fan of the Chicago Bulls, then you need to get your hands on a pair of Air Jordan 3 Retro "Fire Red" 2013. These sneakers are one of four OG colorways of the silhouette and they are sure to make you stand out from the rest. The white tumbled and smooth leather upper is complemented by the signature elephant print in black, while the Fire Red on the midsole, ankle and branding completes the look. The Jumpman on the heel separates it from the launch colorway, making it a must-have for any collection.

title: Air Jordan 3 Retro 'Mocha' 2018
description: Bringing back the color scheme first released in 2001, the Nike Air Jordan 3 Retro "Mocha" complements the white tumbled leather upper with brown elephant print accents. The brown color story is extended to the outsole and Jumpman logo at the heel.

title: Air Jordan 12 Retro 'University Gold'
description: The Nike Air Jordan 12 Retro "University Gold" features a two-tone color scheme with a black leather upper and bright yellow mudguard with lizard patterns. The vibrant yellow extends to the entire length of the sole. Now available in children's sizes.

title: Air Jordan 9 Retro 'UNC'
description: MJ’s Carolina Blue spirit comes to life on the Air Jordan 9 Retro UNC. This men’s shoe delivers a white leather upper with patent navy overlays, complete with pops of University Blue on the Jumpman logos. The perfect addition to your sneaker rotation, this style is sure to turn heads no matter where you go.

title: Air Jordan 8 Retro 'Chrome' 2015
description: The Air Jordan 8 Retro 'Chrome' colorway is back and better than ever! First released in 2003, this colorway is best known for its on-court appearance by Kobe Bryant during the 2003 NBA playoffs. The 'Chrome' colorway features an all-black upper in smooth and perforated nubuck, with chrome detailing on the buckle of the strap. description: The Air Jordan 3 Retro is one of the most popular sneakers on the market. description:

Now, you can own a piece of history with the Air Jordan 3 Retro. This sneaker features all the original details that made the Air Jordan 3 so iconic, like the Jumpman logo and elephant print. The carbon fiber plate and rubber heel wrap are a nod to the world of auto racing, while the chrome eyelets and lace tips add a touch of luxury. Whether you're a die-hard Jordan fan or just looking for a stylish and comfortable pair of sneakers, the Air Jordan 18 OG 'Black Sport Royal' is a great choice.

title: Air Jordan 1 High Retro DMP 'Chicago Bulls'
description: The Air Jordan 1 High Retro DMP 'Chicago Bulls' pays homage to one of basketball legend Michael Jordan's most iconic achievements. In 1986, MJ racked up a staggering 63 points in a single playoff game against the Boston Celtics, setting a new post-season scoring record. To honor this momentous feat, Jordan Brand released a special edition of the Air Jordan 1 in 2009. The 'Chicago Bulls' iteration of the 60+ Pack features a black and red leather upper with an embroidered Jumpman emblem on the heel. The date that Jordan set the 63-point record is emblazoned on the tongue, making this sneaker a must-have for any fan of His Airness.

In 1986, MJ racked up a staggering 63 points in a single playoff game against the Boston Celtics, setting a new post-season scoring record. To honor this momentous feat, Jordan Brand released a special edition of the Air Jordan 1 in 2009. The 'Chicago Bulls' iteration of the 60+ Pack features a black and red leather upper with an embroidered Jumpman emblem on the heel. The date that Jordan set the 63-point record is emblazoned on the tongue, making this sneaker a must-have for any fan of His Airness.

title: Air Jordan 5 Retro DMP 'Raging Bull Pack'
description: The Air Jordan 5 Retro DMP 'Raging Bull Pack' released in 2009 to commemorate Michael Jordan's signature moments. The two shoes were the last silhouette Jordan wore before winning his first title, each with its own unique construction and detailing. One model appears in red, built with premium suede and contrasted by black accents. It is highlighted by reflective silver on the tongue for a touch of style. The other model is finished in black, with red accents and synthetic construction. Both pairs are accented with Jumpman branding on the back heel, an embroidered ‘23’ on the lateral heel, and red-tipped shark tooth detailing on the polyurethane midsole.

title: Air Jordan 11 Retro 'Concord' 2011
description: The Air Jordan 11 Retro 'Concord' 2011 is an iconic sneaker and a re-release of the original that Jordan wore in Game 2 of the 1995 Eastern Conference Finals. The shoe features a white mesh upper with black patent leather overlays and concord branding. The Air Jordan 11 Retro is also the first basketball shoe with a patent leather upper and was famously paired with tuxedos at the 1996 Grammys by Boyz II Men. This shoes recognizable style and elegant look have made it a must-have for sneakerheads and casual wearers alike.

title: Air Jordan 11 Retro 'Platinum Tint'
description: The Nike Air Jordan 11 Retro GS "Platinum Tint" introduces a subdued look featuring light cream shades and red accents. On the upper, patent leather in Platinum Tint overlays the mesh material in Sail. The Jumpman logo and branding come in bright red, bringing focus to the pair.

title: Air Jordan 6 Retro 'Maroon' 2015
description: The Air Jordan 6 Retro 'Maroon' is a classic sneaker that was first released in 1991. It was one of five original colorways of the Air Jordan 6 and is considered to be one of the most iconic sneakers ever designed. The shoe was finally retroed in 2015, after years of fans clamoring for its return. It features classic branding details like the Jumpman logo on the tongue and lace overlay, as well as OG elements like the Nike Air branding on the heel. The clear, translucent outsole is another nod to the original design, and makes this sneaker a must-have for any true fan of Jordan Brand.

title: Air Jordan 6 Retro 'White Infrared' 2014
description: The Air Jordan 6 Retro is one of the most iconic sneakers of all time. First released in 1991, the AJ6 has been retroed several times, most recently in 2014. The design features a white perforated leather upper with infrared accents and a reflective underlay. This shoe is perfect for anyone who wants to add a little bit of old-school style to their wardrobe. Whether you're hitting the court or just hitting the streets, the Air Jordan 6 Retro is a must-have sneaker.

description: This mid-top sneaker is inspired by the traditional "ofrendas" or altars used in the Dia de Muertos celebration, and features a color scheme that resembles marigold flowers. Air Jordan 1 KO 'Low Shadow'
description:
The Air Jordan 1 KO, also known as the AJKO, debuted back in 1986. The “KO” is believed to stand for “knock-off” as in, a cheaper version of the original Air Jordan 1 High. Dressed in a Black, Sail, and Medium Grey color scheme nodding back to the OG “Shadow” release. This offering of the Air Jordan 1 KO Low comes constricted in a full Black and Grey canvas base with Grey suede Swooshes and leather heel overlay. Other details includes “Nike” logos on the tongue tags and insole with Black Wings embroidery on the heels. Black nylon tongues, sizing stamped on the inner lining atop an aged midsole and Black rubber outsole completes the design.
DX4981-002

title: Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'Craft Vibrations Of Naija'
Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG x Marvel 'Spider-Man: Across the Spider-Verse'
description:
Nike and Jordan Brand are returning back to the Spider-Verse for their second Spider-Man themed Air Jordan 1, with the release of the Air Jordan 1 High OG Spider-Man Across the Spider-Verse.The Jordan 1 High OG Spider-Man Across the Spider-Verse is the next iteration of the original Air Jordan 1 Chicago colorway. description: The Air Jordan 7 Retro was first released in 2008 as part of the "Countdown" pack. It was a re-release of the original Air Jordan 7s which were released in 1991. The 2015 "Hare Jordan" collection was released in conjunction with the 23rd anniversary of the Air Jordan 7's original release. The Air Jordan 7 Retro is a must-have for any Jordan fan or sneakerhead. It features a clean, simple design that is both stylish and iconic. The shoe is made with high-quality materials and construction, and it includes classic Jordan branding details.

title: Air Jordan 7 Retro 'Olympic' 2012
description: The Air Jordan 7 Retro 'Olympic' is back for 2012, and it's better than ever. This iconic sneaker was originally released in 1992, and it was worn by Michael Jordan as he led the USA "Dream Team" to a gold medal at the Olympic Games. The design features a white and metallic silver upper with accents from Obsidian, metallic gold, and True Red. The sneaker was released in July 2012 and includes the Olympic Jersey number '9' on the heel. If you're a fan of MJ or the USA Dream Team, this is a must-have sneaker for your collection.

title: Air Jordan 18 OG 'Black Sport Royal' 2003
description: Released in February 2003, the Air Jordan 18 OG 'Black Sport Royal' was the last model that Michael Jordan wore on an NBA court. Designed by Jordan Brand's senior footwear designer Tate Kuerbis, the AJ18 took inspiration from the worlds of auto racing and fine Italian dress shoes. The carbon fiber plate and rubber heel wrap are a nod to the world of auto racing, while the chrome eyelets and lace tips add a touch of luxury. Whether you're a die-hard Jordan fan or just looking for a stylish and comfortable pair of sneakers, the Air Jordan 18 OG 'Black Sport Royal' is a great choice.

title: SoleFly x Air Jordan 10 Retro '10th Anniversary'
description: Nike and Miami-based retailer SoleFly have teamed up to release the SoleFly x Air Jordan 10 Retro '10th Anniversary' sneaker. This special edition shoe celebrates SoleFly's first decade in business, and pays tribute to Miami's Freedom Tower with its two-tone Sail and beige upper, newsprint graphic outsole, and unique branding hits. The perfect sneaker for any Jordan or SoleFly fan, this limited edition shoe is sure to turn heads whether you're on the court or just hitting the streets.

title: Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Wild Things'

The rest of the upper is built with tan leather and a quartet of color-popped eyelets in neon green, pink, blue and red. A second Jumpman logo embellishes a molded heel panel in dark beige. The sneaker sits on a two-tone foam midsole, supported by an outsole built with gum rubber under the forefoot and heel.

title: Travis Scott x Air Jordan 6 Retro 'British Khaki'
description: The Nike TDTravis Scott x Air Jordan 6 Retro British Khaki is a scaled-down version of the highly coveted collaboration between Travis Scott and Air Jordan. This mid-top sneaker is outfitted in a tan suede upper, with stash pouches on either side of the collar paying homage to Scott's "Cactus Jack" nickname. The bright crimson accents on the Jumpman branding on the tongue and the mismatched Nike and Cactus Jack logos on each heel are a nice touch. The soft foam midsole provides ample cushioning, while the glow-in-the-dark rubber outsole adds a bit of fun and functionality.

title: Air Jordan 12 Utility 'Grind'
description: Looking for a pair of shoes that are both stylish and sustainable? Look no further than the Air Jordan 12 Retro Utility GS "Grind"! These grade-school sneakers are constructed with tumbled leather and nubuck, finished in black with stitched detailing and Bright Crimson accents. A heel pull-loop makes them easy to put on and take off, while full-length Zoom Air cushioning provides a comfortable ride. And best of all, they feature Nike Grind rubber outsoles made from recycled material - perfect for the eco-conscious shopper. Whether you're hitting the court or just running errands, the Air Jordan 12 Retro Utility GS "Grind" has you covered in style!

Air Jordan 1 KO 'Low Shadow'
description:
The Air Jordan 1 KO, also known as the AJKO, debuted back in 1986. The “KO” is believed to stand for “knock-off” as in, a cheaper version of the original Air Jordan 1 High. Dressed in a Black, Sail, and Medium Grey color scheme nodding back to the OG “Shadow” release. This offering of the Air Jordan 1 KO Low comes constricted in a full Black and Grey canvas base with Grey suede Swooshes and leather heel overlay. Other details includes “Nike” logos on the tongue tags and insole with Black Wings embroidery on the heels. Black nylon tongues, sizing stamped on the inner lining atop an aged midsole and Black rubber outsole completes the design.

The limited edition sneakers are constructed using various leathers, suedes, and other premium materials across the uppers. The patterns used across the sneakers are designed to mimic the Miles Morales/Spider-Man animation style.

title: Air Jordan 1 Mid SE 'Motorsport'
description: Looking for a shoe that's as cool as it is stylish? Look no further than the Air Jordan 1 Mid Motorsport BP. This kids-exclusive release is inspired by Michael Jordan's love of auto racing, and it shows in the vibrant hues and unique details. The upper is made from diamond-textured white synthetic leather, with nubby textures on the forefoot and heel overlay. The Swoosh and collar flap are done in matching gold, with a red Wings logo on the lateral side. Additional branding elements include '23' imprinted on the forefoot and a checkerboard Jordan decal atop the heel.The durable rubber cupsole provides lasting comfort and style.

title: Air Jordan 1 Mid SE 'Motorsport'
description: Looking for a trendy and stylish sneaker for your little one? Then check out the Air Jordan 1 Mid SE TD ‘Motorsport’! This unique and cool sneaker is inspired by Michael Jordan’s love of motorcycle racing, and features a white synthetic leather upper with a subtle diamond texture. The forefoot and heel overlays are in Gym Red and University Gold, while the lateral side features the ‘23’ stamp. The back heel has a checkerboard Jordan decal, and the whole sneaker sits on a standard rubber cupsole. Your little one will love showing off this stylish new sneaker!
